{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_57","type":"agent_message","text":"Added the missing reflection entry under the owning artifact, not `jetty-servlets`: [metadata/org.eclipse.jetty/jetty-http/index.json](/home/vjovanov/c/forge/forge1/graalvm-reachability-metadata/forge/local_repositories/forge_worktrees/3128-472750d8/metadata/org.eclipse.jetty/jetty-http/index.json:1) now includes metadata version `11.0.24`, and [metadata/org.eclipse.jetty/jetty-http/11.0.24/reachability-metadata.json](/home/vjovanov/c/forge/forge1/graalvm-reachability-metadata/forge/local_repositories/forge_worktrees/3128-472750d8/metadata/org.eclipse.jetty/jetty-http/11.0.24/reachability-metadata.json:1) registers `org.eclipse.jetty.http.pathmap.PathSpecSet.<init>()` with condition `org.eclipse.jetty.util.IncludeExcludeSet`. `checkMetadataFiles` rejected that entry under `jetty-servlets` because its allowed packages are only `org.eclipse.jetty.servlets`, so moving it to `jetty-http` was required.\n\nI also changed the test helper at [Jetty_servletsTest.java](/home/vjovanov/c/forge/forge1/graalvm-reachability-metadata/forge/local_repositories/forge_worktrees/3128-472750d8/tests/src/org.eclipse.jetty/jetty-servlets/11.0.24/src/test/java/org_eclipse_jetty/jetty_servlets/Jetty_servletsTest.java:267) to use the existing raw-socket request path instead of `HttpURLConnection`. The `http` URL protocol issue is not expressible in reachability metadata, so this keeps verification focused on metadata instead of a test-only native-image flag.\n\nVerification used the required GraalVM:\n`native-image 25.0.2 2026-01-20`\nand both commands passed:\n`./gradlew checkMetadataFiles -Pcoordinates=org.eclipse.jetty:jetty-servlets:11.0.24`\n`./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=org.eclipse.jetty:jetty-servlets:11.0.24`\n\nPre-existing local change in `tests/src/org.eclipse.jetty/jetty-servlets/11.0.24/user-code-filter.json` was left untouched."}}
